ehicle-wrap-cost-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Full pricing details →</a></p><h2>Fleet Wraps by Industry</h2><div class="grid"><img alt="HVAC fleet wrap Chicago" loading="lazy" src="/images/499031832_24357754093827647_8285045186686109093_n.webp"/><img alt="Electrician fleet wrap Chicago" loading="lazy" src="/images/arnold_electric_truck.webp"/><img alt="Commercial fleet van wrap Chicago" loading="lazy" src="/images/499031832_24357754093827647_8285045186686109093_n.webp"/><img alt="Moving company fleet wrap Chicago" loading="lazy" src="/images/windy_city_box_truck.webp"/></div><p class="body-text"><a href="/portfolio/" style="color:var(--gold)">View full fleet portfolio →</a></p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-item"><h3>How much do fleet wraps cost in Chicago?</h3><p>Pricing depends on vehicle type: cargo vans $2,800–$4,500, sprinters $3,500–$5,200, box trucks $4,200–$10,000, pickups $2,200–$3,800. Volume discounts of 5–15% apply for fleets of 3+ vehicles.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Who needs fleet wraps?</h3><p>Any business with 3+ vehicles: HVAC, plumbing, electrical, contracting, delivery, moving, landscaping, and any service business with vehicles on the road daily.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>How does the fleet rollout process work?</h3><p>We create a master design template, then wrap 1–3 vehicles at a time in phases so your fleet stays operational. A 10-vehicle fleet typically completes in 4–6 weeks.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Are fleet wraps tax deductible?</h3><p>Yes — fleet wraps are 100% tax deductible as a business advertising expense under IRS Section 179. The full cost can be deducted in the year of installation.</p></div></div>